cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use ZPE Prosody artifacts or results, cite this repository record.
  This is a private staging lane and not a public release surface.
type: software
title: "ZPE Prosody: Zero-Point Encoding Prosody Lane (Private Staging)"
authors:
  - given-names: Zer0pa
    family-names: Architect-Prime
  - name: Zer0pa Labs
repository-code: https://github.com/Zer0pa/ZPE-Prosody
url: https://github.com/Zer0pa/ZPE-Prosody
license: LicenseRef-Zer0pa-SAL-6.0
abstract: >-
  ZPE Prosody is a private staging repository for the ZPE Prosody Wave-1
  lane. It focuses on prosody compression, retrieval, and transfer using
  ZPE directional-encoding primitives. This repo does not represent a
  public release surface and does not cover other ZPE lanes.
keywords:
  - prosody encoding
  - speech compression
  - zero-point encoding
  - evidence discipline
  - falsification-first
